# Architecture Guardrails

- Respect system roles:
  - `frontend/` (Next.js + TypeScript + Tailwind): UI, chat interaction, results display.
  - `backend/` (FastAPI): business rules, copay computation, ranking orchestration, AI integration.
  - Supabase/Postgres (`database/` + DB access): persistence, auth, coverage/service/hospital data.
- Keep business logic in backend services, not UI components.
- Keep DB-specific assumptions centralized and documented when changing schema or queries.

## Integration rules

- Frontend should consume backend/Supabase APIs, not duplicate copay or ranking logic.
- Backend endpoints should be deterministic for core calculations and easy to test with sample data.
- Schema or coverage rule changes must include corresponding updates to local sample data and docs.
